-- Monte Paschi shares rise on bargain hunting - traders
-- 
-- Wed Mar 05, 2014 08:21AM EST
-- None



MILAN, March 5 (Reuters) - Shares in Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena <BMPS.MI> rose more than 6 percent on Wednesday as traders said people were buying the stock because it was seen as cheap.

By 1311 GMT, the shares rose 6.7 percent to 0.1968 euros, while the European bank index <.SX7P> was up 0.45 percent. "The stock has remained behind," a Milan-based trader said.